commit 837e171d251651c642fa59527e1323b6b60c6f56
Author: Gergely Nagy <algernon@bonehunter.rulez.org>
Date:   Sat Apr 26 14:16:04 2003 +0000

    Fixed procmail subject coloring
    
    * src/mod_procmail.c (ccze_procmail_process): If the header field is
      Subject or Folder, put out space2 with the same color. This fixes the
      problem where the first set of whitespace in a multi-word subject were
      coloured with the default color.
    * testsuite/bug-procmailsubj2.test: New test.
    * testsuite/bug-procmailsubj2.in: New input file.
    * testsuite/bug-procmailsubj2.ok: New expected output.
    * testsuite/Makefile.in (TESTS): Added bug-procmailsubj2.test.
    
    Problem was noticed by Alan Schmitt, who also provided the sample input
    to trigger the bug.
    
    git-archimport-id: algernon@bonehunter.rulez.org--iluvatar-archive/ccze--0.3--patch-11

M	ChangeLog
M	src/mod_procmail.c
M	testsuite/Makefile.in
A	testsuite/bug-procmailsubj2.in
A	testsuite/bug-procmailsubj2.ok
A	testsuite/bug-procmailsubj2.test

commit 996c2f5909a872a8887c480169fe7b36e1e9856d
Author: Gergely Nagy <algernon@bonehunter.rulez.org>
Date:   Sat Apr 26 14:10:17 2003 +0000

    Fixed the testsuite
    
    * testsuite/do-test: Compare with ${srcdir}/${testname}.ok and .errok,
      instead of ./${testname}.ok. This way make check will not silently
      pass in a separate objtree.
    * testsuite/bug-httpd.ok: Regenerated.
    * testsuite/bug-procmailsubj.ok: Likewise.
    * testsuite/bug-procmailsubj.test: Add -p procmail to the CCZE
      commandline.
    
    git-archimport-id: algernon@bonehunter.rulez.org--iluvatar-archive/ccze--0.3--patch-10

M	ChangeLog
M	testsuite/bug-httpd.ok
M	testsuite/bug-procmailsubj.ok
M	testsuite/bug-procmailsubj.test
M	testsuite/do-test

